{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"5324","heading":"Statement of policy","label":"5324 Statement of policy","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s5324","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/ch62/schII/ptA","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs5324","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s5324/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s5324","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs5324%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"increasing growth in the developing world is a major goal of international economic policy;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s5324/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s5324","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs5324%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"it is necessary to broaden the range of options in dealing with the debt problem to include improved mechanisms to restructure existing debt;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s5324/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s5324","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs5324%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"active consideration of a new multilateral authority to improve the management of the debt problem and to share the burdens of adjustment more equitably must be undertaken; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s5324/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s5324","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs5324%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"countries with strong current account surpluses bear a major responsibility for providing the financial resources needed for growth in the developing world.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
